# footnote_wired.lt -- pins the Lout output mdlout produces for a
# pandoc-style footnote in PDF mode: a numbered superscript followed
# by Lout's @FootNote so the page-bottom note placement is handled
# downstream by doc setup. The same body reused twice still gets the
# same number (idempotent assignment via _fn_order).
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A claim with a footnote{ "[1]" } @Sup {} @FootNote { First footnote body. }.
Another claim referencing the same note{ "[1]" } @Sup {} @FootNote { First footnote body. }.
@PP
A second, named footnote{ "[2]" } @Sup {} @FootNote { Body of the second note. }
appears later.
@End @Text
